First, **1111111** is not a valid `Timestamp` format, it should look like this {&quot;xxx.Name-xxx-**2019-10-08 09:00:00**&quot;:&quot;100&quot;}.  

Second, use **Jackson** API to parse the JSON string to get key and value fields.  

Third, I assume the prefix of timestamp value is **xxx.Name-xxx-**, then you can retrieve it (says **2019-10-08 09:00:00**) by using `String.replace()`.  

Sample code:

    String jsonStr = &quot;{\&quot;xxx.Name-xxx-2019-10-08 09:00:00\&quot;:\&quot;100\&quot;}&quot;;
         
    ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();
    for (Iterator&lt;Map.Entry&lt;String, JsonNode&gt;&gt; it = mapper.readTree(jsonStr).fields(); it.hasNext();) {
        Map.Entry&lt;String, JsonNode&gt; field = it.next();
        String key = field.getKey();
        int value = field.getValue().asInt();
        System.out.println(&quot;key:       &quot; + key);
        System.out.println(&quot;value:     &quot; + value);
             
        Timestamp timestamp = Timestamp.valueOf(key.replace(&quot;xxx.Name-xxx-&quot;, &quot;&quot;));
